~bShell Commands~B

There is a group of commands for accessing the shell.  Following is the list:

    ~bKeys        Command         Description~B

    ~#uC-x `~U       ~uinsertPipe~U      Execute shell pipeline and insert its output
                                into current buffer at point, without moving
                                point if n == 0.

    ~#uC-x |~U       ~upipeBuf~U         Feed current buffer through shell pipeline and
                                read its output into current buffer, with same
                                options as ~ureadFile~U command.

    ~#uC-x ~~~U       ~ureadPipe~U        Execute shell pipeline and read its output into
                                current buffer, with same options as ~ureadFile~U
                                command.

    ~#uC-x $~U       ~ushell~U           Spawn an interactive shell session.

    ~#uC-x !~U       ~ushellCmd~U        Execute a shell command and display result in a
                                pop-up window.
